output:
I walked on down by the old canal Where the memories flowed
I sat and thought where it all went wrong So very long ago
I remember it too well Oh, I remember it too well
I came upon the old log house Where once we made our plans
But now it looks overgrown with time And the nettles stun my hands
I remember it too well Oh, I remember it too well
I remember it too well
Further down was our favourite spot Beneath the sheltering trees
And I began to cry for what Was never meant to be
I remember it too well Oh, I remember it too well
